			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">From the Enchanter thread:
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Aggro from spells that a mob is immune to - I was told this should be pretty easy to fix. They were a bit surpised at this one. It's on the list now! 
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Urk. A lot of us who <span style="font-style: italic">want</span> snap aggro from spells that MOBs are immune to (e.g., immune to run speed changes, immune to fear, level-immune to stuns) would be, uh, kinda bummed if this is changed.
<br />

<br />
And hey, sometimes we're trying to get that aggro off an Enchanter. <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" /><br />_________________<br />Bangzoom
<br />
65th Ranger of Doomnation
<br />
Veteran Crew Through and Through</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
