			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><a href="http://www.thesteelwarrior.org/forum/showthread.php?t=7457" target="_blank">http://www.thesteelwarrior.org/forum/showthread.php?t=7457</a>
<br />

<br />
Steel Warriors write up:
<br />

<br />
So I'm back from San Diego. What a trip that was. It was good though, I'm really glad Sony decided to do this. The level of communication and interaction we had with the team on Saturday was just unbelievable. 
<br />

<br />
I got the feeling that these guys had broken free from marketting finally and were ready to fix the game. They openly said that GoD was released based on a level raise (70) which would have gone live with GoD, and then another with Omens. You want to know something else? Marketting considers Velious to be their worst performing expansion, while...drumroll please...Legacy of Ykesha is the best performing expansion. From a marketting point of view, maybe this is true. But I think if you ask the players, LoY was a gimmick expansion while Velious was, in my opinion, the best and most complete expansion they've released yet.
<br />

<br />
The developers are passionate, they asked so many questions. Even after the meetings I was getting asked what about this, or this. They forked out a lot of money this weekend. They also took a huge risk. When you invite 50+ people who've been playing this game for years and watched it's highs and it's lows -- it's amazing they didn't a barbed wire fence with armed guards and mine fields out there. But it wasn't. It was 3 buildings, with an SOE sign out front. I think Thomas called it "Sony's weekend with it's pants down" - because nothing was hidden from us. We saw it all..from the GM pit to EverQuest II to Omens of War models and new epics and the new servers that will be powering EverQuest soon. 
<br />

<br />
What I'm trying to say is...These guys deserve a chance. They love this game and they're tired of where it's been headed. Read over these and keep an open mind that this is obviously not "a CD, 2 books, 20 printed pages, and a manifesto." 
<br />

<br />
Anyway enough of that, heres what you guys are really after...
<br />

<br />
This list is from a letter given to us today after the EQ team met to discuss what they'd heard in our individual meetings. Keep in mind this isn't a final list or even close to it. They got a ton of information today, and this is more of a "to do" list for the time being while they finish going through it all.
<br />

<br />
Comments in Red are mine.
<br />

<br />
Quote:
<br />
Dear Guild and Community Representatives,
<br />

<br />
Thank you very much for a great Summit! By all accounts it was a huge success. I can speak for the EverQuest Development Team and tell you that we're all grateful for the input you provided. In fact, in trying to generate this list to giove you this evening, we realized there was so much to go over that we wouldn't be able to get a complete list together in time. We're committed to not only listening to your feedback, but working with you to make EverQuest more enjoyable for years to come.
<br />

<br />
So, we decided to list the Top Ten themes we would address starting Monday, as well as the most common themes that we'll come back with more information on by mid-week next week.
<br />

<br />
A quick discussion resulted in a list of items that we will immediately address:
<br />

<br />
Add scripting to shut off empty instances of Plane of Time
<br />
This is the first step towards them fully instancing time
<br />
Raid Messages of the day
<br />
Improving how we handle beta and the testing process
<br />
John Smedley appologized for how this was handled in GoD. BetaBuff didn't sound like it would be around much longer.
<br />
Increase the number of debuffs allowed on MOBs
<br />
Increase buffs on players through AAs
<br />
Yay.
<br />
Note field on raid window
<br />
Improved consent & drag for raid, group, and guild
<br />
This includes /consent for Raid, Group, and Guild. Other things mentioned were the ability to drag multiple corpses.
<br />
Improve corpse drag radius
<br />
Make charms not no-drop
<br />
Guild and individual rewards for guild beta testing
<br />
Work on larger To Do list...I know this one is a little random
<br />

<br />
Future items we will immediately begin looking at and discussing are as follows:
<br />

<br />
Plane of Time instancing and other issues
<br />
Back flagging solutions to help with high-end guild atrophy
<br />
This is a great one. Ideas thrown around were guild flags, extra flags, 85/15 rule everywhere, etc.
<br />
Improved raid and guild functionality
<br />
Ideas brought up were Secondary/Tertiary assists, /assist raid being the same range as /assist, drag and drop groupmaking in the raid window.
<br />
Auto loot all for your corpse
<br />
Improvements to raid XP
<br />
Review the epic 2.0 quests
<br />
They are thinking of making these a progressive type quest (think coldain ring)
<br />
No more alien NPCs <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" /> (focusing more on familiar Norrathian themes)
<br />
Solo LDON-Style instances or similar content
<br />
Issues with item augmentations
<br />
I believe this includes focii
<br />
Possible enhancement to guild wars
<br />

<br />
Of course these aren't all of items. You brought us a CD, 2 books, 20 printed sheets, and a manifesto. We'll need to go through all of those and our notes before we can really get a good tally of all the wonderful ideas and questions that were presented.
<br />

<br />
THank you again for your feedback and participation. WE've had a great weekend and a wonderful display of things to come.
<br />

<br />
Sincerely,
<br />
Robert Pfister
<br />
Executive Producer
<br />
EverQuest
<br />

<br />
And the EverQuest Development Team!  
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
There were quite a few other issues raised obviously. This is just the first step, and I wouldn't be surprised if these things start to go live within 2 weeks.
<br />

<br />
A few other things not mentioned but probably should be:
<br />

<br />
AA requirements for being able to level in Omens were called "rumors".
<br />
They are going to pick a raid number and stay with it. (Got the feeling it would be 54).
<br />
OOW will only have a very small number (I was told 1) of locked zones. The end encounters will be locked, but anyone will be free to go into the zone.
<br />
Boots of Despair - The taunt mod does work for us.
<br />
Inspect Buffs Leader AA should show your own buff timers as well.
<br />
There are new armor sets coming to ldon which will be elemental-calibre. The price cap at 1452 will be raised, to what I don't know.
<br />
You will be able to remove your augments from your armor soon.
<br />
Some GoD spells will be available via quest.
<br />
They are considering outsourcing the artwork to an outside company so they're more free to work on content, while still having unique models. I believe they said PoP was outsourced, for example.
<br />
Veeshans Peak revamp is coming very soon. When I asked if the old key would be needed, I was told: "You take the old key, and some new stuff, and make the new key -- then you get a reward for your old key."
<br />
The Customer service system is being improved (And has improved) quite a bit.
<br />
Lots of talk of improving LDON for the more casual or smaller numbered raiders, and possibly creating an alternate progression path to elemental -&gt; time with this.
<br />
They seem to want to instance most/all progression targets. This is good.
<br />
Guild Banking seems to be on the way.
<br />
Brenlo wants a halfling bard.
<br />
Hobart asked about any interest in an in-game DKP client
<br />
New animations at the end of the year..along with that is possible new race/class combinations (not new races/classes, just new combo's)
<br />
Shaun Lord who worked on PoP was added back to the EQ Live team this weekend (that's a good thing)
<br />
The majority of EQ players are between levels 30- 50.
<br />
Eq is NT based.
<br />
BiC quest pieces off Primals will be changed.
<br />
Ikkinz trials are being changed a bit - for knight survivability.
<br />
Epic 1.5's. These are designed more for Time-level people, while 2.0's are aimed at the endgame.
<br />

<br />
That was all raised in the development meetings. We also had a customer service meeting though, which went pretty well.
<br />
There will be a GM Graveyard Shift soon
<br />
A new tool is available to the GM staff, CS Assist. This increases their efficiency quite a bit.
<br />
As part of CS Assist, GM's can do a few new things. They can leave you persistant messages - Meaning you can logout, and tomorrow you'll log in to an answered petition. Going along with that, they can reimburse items to off-line accounts.
<br />
The Guide program will be changing directions a little bit. They'll be primarily responsible for running events and roleplay quests throughout the game, and will help with smaller petitions if needbe. This should increase the number of GM events and random events happening ingame around you.
<br />

<br />
I also recieved a packet labelled "The Legion of Mata Muram". It includes some things about OOW lore and features.
<br />

<br />
Quote:
<br />
The Legend of Mata Muram
<br />

<br />
Everyone has learned that Mata Muram, the leader of the legion, is a terrible creature that seeks to build an ultimate army by any means necessary -- including stealing beings from other worlds.
<br />

<br />
Mata Muram is much older than almost every member of his army and is well protected. He is described by the Muramites as unmerciful, powerful, and a worthy leader -- though there are rumors that he is obsessed with revenge -- against who they don't know. Some Muramites have been overheard describing Mata Muram as some sort of Dragon.
<br />

<br />
No one knows when the Realm of Discord and its counterpart, the Realm of Order, came into existence. Both in the Realm of Discord and Realm of Order there are rulers that are all-knowing and all-seeing that can never be seen or touched, much like the Nameless.
<br />

<br />
Follow the Wayfarers Brotherhood to the war-ravaged Realm of Discord to help end the tyrannical ways of the Muramites once and for all. Adventure solo, in groups, and raids to complete "epic quests" and earn prestigious weapons to aide in your battles. Take your character to new levels of p;ower and aquire new items, spells, and quests.
<br />

<br />
Features
<br />

<br />
-Discover rich new zones with detailed environments featuring expanded graphical elements, improved spell effects, and all-new monsters to fight.
<br />
-Develop your character beyond level 65. Unlock new innovative items, powerful spells, and thrilling quests.
<br />
-Earn specialized, hand-tailored Epic Weapons with the completion of any of 16 epic quests. New epic quests will challenge even the toughest and most experienced Norrathians as they journey alone or in raid groups to win these valuable items. Designed for higher level players, each weapon will be unique in design and will have specialized characteristics.
<br />
-Enhanced tribute system allows yolu to turn your loot into favor points for your whole guild to enjoy.
<br />
-Allows players to go to various zones and request quick and easy tasks to gain experience and collect cool loot.
<br />
-Recieve exciting new Custom PC Titles for your characters. Accomplish a variety of missions and get bestowed a title added toi your characters name.
<br />
-New Alternate Advancement Abilities with unique skills to master.
<br />
-New tradeskill recipes to produce hundreds of new items.
<br />
-Dozens of new and exciting story-driven quests for the hardy adventurer  
<br />

<br />

<br />
There's also some concept art of....epic 2.0's in this packet. They look really pretty badass I have to say. I saw most of the ones they have semi-finished and these things are beautiful. With DX9 they've added a lot more intricate designs into them, and the etchings mostly glow even when it's dark all around - it's cool stuff.
<br />

<br />
The warrior one was still really rough, and all I can really tell you from what I saw is that it was a sword, and not a flaming axe.<br />_________________<br /><span style="font-size: 14px; line-height: normal"><span style="color: purple">Kestri Evensong</span></span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
