			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><a href="http://www.shadowedsoul.com/forums/showthread.php?t=11925" target="_blank">http://www.shadowedsoul.com/forums/showthread.php?t=11925</a>
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
- The level cap was originally supposed to be raised to L70 prior to Gates of Discords launch. This in part can explain why it was so difficult at first. We now wont see L70 until Omens releases.
<br />

<br />
- Legacy of Ykesha was the best selling expansion (Bank space!) while Velious was the worst selling. I have a feeling LoY is probably the least used expansion zone wise though although Sony claims that most of their customers are between L30 and L50.
<br />

<br />
- Omens will most likely be tested by the higher end guilds en masse. Previously high end guilds were represented here and there but because entire guilds were not brought in it was very difficult to get a good test of content since people werent used to working together.
<br />

<br />
- Smedley also mentioned that one of his largest regrets is naming EQ2 after Everquest since they consider them entirely different games that will co-exist for quite a long time.
<br />

<br />
...
<br />

<br />
- 1018's exist to keep people from exploiting encounters. Instead of being able to cut link when a fight goes south, the server will fight for you for several minutes. At the absolute maximum you should never experience 1018's for longer than 10 minutes. Jamey did mention they may look into putting in checks for whether or not a character is on a hate list and then shorten the 1018 length accordingly to cover those legit linkdeaths.
<br />

<br />
- Its highly unlikely that Everquest will ever been made zoneless. Initial tests with the technology in SWG have proven that it takes alot more memory and tends to create a good bit more instability than its worth. As proof its common knowledge that the SWG servers still reboot nearly every morning due to memory fragmentation and the like.
<br />

<br />
- The bug with the main assist raid ability losing its targetting circle after the MA dies and resses back in would be looked into. Currently we work around it by just turning it off and back on again.
<br />

<br />
- Being able to invite someone to raid or group across zones is technically possible but for CoH/Corpse summoning exploit reasons is not allowed. From my conversation with Ryan Barker who is in charge of spells though SoE may consider changing this policy. We'll have to see.
<br />

<br />
- Everquest is not optimized for Nvidia or ATI. The performance differences we can see in side by side comparison are more often than not the result of the two hardware companies own drivers. Its a well known fact that ATI has had issues with the quality of their drivers in the past.
<br />

<br />
- Its possible that a bug exists in the range check code for spell casting. Allegedly if a buff cast is started on someone and they run out of range the out of range text appears but the spell gem greys out as if the cast was successful and naturally the target doesnt get the buff. Im not sure if this happens with all buffs but DI and Ferocity were cited as culprits by the other guildleader who brought it up. Jamey took some notes and will look into it.
<br />

<br />
- We spoke a bit about the guest flag system and about some of the reasons why it might bug itself from time to time. I explained that very often when we zoned from one area where we were using guest flags to another zone we needed to use them we many times had to rebuild the raid to reset the flags. Jamey explained that the memory space the flag system resides in might be getting overwritten by another process and jumbling it up. No commitment was made to look into it but now that hes aware of it we can hope.
<br />

<br />
- The "screenshots" put up for Omens of War are not actually screenshots of the expansion at all which is really good news since it just looked like more of the same from Gates. Jamey explained that the screenshots were actually screenshots of the Forgotten Halls the DX9 test zone you can access from Nerindia's Landing meant to show the new effects we can expect in Omens of War.
<br />

<br />
...
<br />

<br />
Development
<br />
===========
<br />

<br />
- Artificial Intelligence: They realize that right now the system is pretty much just "Rawr, Im mad at you so Im going to hit you." They would love to put a more involved AI system into the game and its something we might see in the future though its unlikely it will get in with Omens.
<br />

<br />
- Chain and Infection spells: Currently being played with and some early examples are allegedly even in the game now according to Jason (missed last name) one of the developers we had sitting with us for dinner that night. Apparently there is an encounter where you are charmed and part of the charm makes you proc a spell that will charm the people you are attacking. This is an example of the Infection spells. The chain spells are a little different and as they pertain to a heal spell would jump in a line from the caster to the target and then a set number of targets behind the first target. This might add some new tactics into the way raiders position themselves which would be interesting.
<br />

<br />
- Increased buff slots: Ryan mentioned that there may be some AA in future expansions for certain classes to expand their buff slots. When asked if we could move MGB heals to the bard box he was fairly firm on not allowing that as the entire idea of the box was only for bard spells. Furthermore when asked if we could have a debuff box then so we didnt lose buff slots during raids to AE he felt that was part of balacing those encounters.
<br />

<br />
- Ritual Spells/Combo System: An interesting idea that might be implemented in the distant future. Three to four different classes would get together to do some powerful spell casting or melee move. Not too much detail was available on the system since they are in the very very early stages of discussing it but it could potentially remove some of the tedium and hit "A" and go afk from raids.
<br />

<br />
- Debuff slots: Mobs will likely have their number of slots increased again. Ryan agreed that it sucked for the necros/shaman/druids to not all be able to contribute damage because the mob ran out of debuff slots.
<br />

<br />
- Improved invis: It might become targettable so we can CR in GoD a little easier. Furthermore the LDoN potion that has a fixed duration on it instead of random may have its components made more common. Failing that we may see Improved Invis potions and they might even stack. Clerics/Chionia rejoice!
<br />

<br />
- PBAE & Pillar spells: I asked if wizards could get some new PBAE and Pillar spells with the Omens expansion. Ryan stated that it was likely we would get new versions of both types of spells and that the list up on Lucy will be heavily changed in the near future. It was mostly just a groundwork list to get the ball rolling.
<br />

<br />
- LDoN raids/Future raid sizes: Akil mentioned that LDoN raids were really just an afterthought which is why we have some of the raid size issues we're experiencing with the expansion. It was pretty much confirmed by everyone I talked to that SoE will be settling in on 54 as the raid size for the future.
<br />

<br />
- Omens of War: Presently it only has one locked zone. That is not to say that just anyone will be able to be successful in all the zones. Many of the zones will have high level mobs out in the middle of the zone that we'll be able to test ourselves on periodically as we level up to 70.
<br />

<br />
- Collision: The collision fixes in conjunction with the DX9 upgrade should have made performance on lower end machines much better in water zones and areas where we typically levitate.
<br />

<br />
- Planes of Power had a longer development schedule than the other expansions. In addition a good portion of the artwork involved was outsourced which let SoE concentrate on adding more content than usual. It was stressed that we much preferred this and Ryan mentioned that SoE was doing some preliminary work with other Art houses for future expansions so they can possibly repeat the success of PoP.
<br />

<br />
- New 6/8 Augments: Discussed several options for allowing Augments to be removed from gear without destroying them. The first way that was explained involved a new UI window that would allow you to use hefty amounts of plat to pay for their removal. Another option that was discussed was to just make them Inventory items that could be moved around at will. It sounded like the plat sink was more likely. An attendee also asked if it was possible to have an augment birdfeeder added to PoK. The devs couldnt see any immediate issues with doing so.
<br />

<br />
Customer Support
<br />
==============
<br />

<br />
- CS assist, the new petition system should begin reducing petition times extensively as the CS staff learn to use it and further features are added to it. Presently they claim the average petition length is 33 hours. 
<br />

<br />
- One such new system is the persistant message system which allows GM's to leave you messages even while you are offline to answer your petitions. Furthermore the new CS assist system keeps petitions active across patches and reboots so you dont have to keep petitioning over and over.
<br />

<br />
- Another new system is the Guild Critical system which will allow Guild Leaders to submit petitions for priority response within 15-30 minutes on several issues. These issues include Spawn Disputes, Raid Disruption (Training, Harassment, Kill Stealing, Leap Frogging, Ninjalooting), Character Flag Issues (NPC being under the world or not spawning), Incorrect Event functionality. This system is in its pilot stages right now and we'll be testing it out over the next few weeks before they decide to build it into the CS assist interface.
<br />

<br />
- George also mentioned that their new tiering system in conjunction with their outsourcing of Tier 1 petitions to their overseas GM's should allow quicker response on Tier 2 and 3 petitions such as those mentioned in the Guild Critical system and item loss petitions. He further went on to say that the overseas GMs were quickly picking up the game and learning how to more effectively handle petitions. He acknowledged that it was rough at first and that the US CS team has also had to learn which petitions can be sent overseas and which need to be handled here in the US. The category system in the CS assist tool is helping them direct the petitions accordingly.
<br />

<br />
This post is starting to get a little long so I'll come back and add things as I go through my notes and memory further. 
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
